post_text: On: The Importance of Choosing The Best Childcare, Pre School for your Child ♡
shared_text:
First Things First
February 25, 2015 at 10:13 AM ·

Quality is an important factor to consider in choosing a child care or preschool program, but it’s not always easy to spot. Things to look for/questions to ask include:

• Is the teacher at eye level with the kids when they are interacting?
• Are there books and other materials to encourage learning within the children’s reach?
• How are families kept informed about their child’s progress?

Our quality checklist can help you make a more informed decision when considering a child care or preschool setting for your child. Download it at: http://www.qualityfirstaz.com/parents-and-families/tools-to-help-you-choose/
